title: Memoirs of the Life of Sir Walter Scott, Volume 6
author: Lockhart, J. G. (John Gibson)
snippet: We hunted all over Huntly wood, and so on to Halidon     and Prieston--saw twelve hares, and killed six, having very hard     runs, and tiring three packs of grews completely.
